<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="132" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1305,1908]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1305,1330]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">Description.</emphasis>
Body (
<figureCitation box="[385,451,1305,1329]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. a – d" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1253,1276]" captionTargetBox="[195,1386,213,1213]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1409,193,1232]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 1. a – d. Kapsa (Rigida? aculeiformis Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; e – h. Kapsa (Rigida) apicispina Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; i – l. Kapsa (Rigida) brevis Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; m – q. Kapsa (Rigida? explanata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222871/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[441,451,1305,1329]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" unit="m" value="1.0">1</quantity>
</figureCitation>
m, n) light brownish, central part of vertex and pronotum, mesonotum and clavus of forewing brown, forming longitudinal dark stripe on dorsum. Coronal suture (
<figureCitation box="[1050,1117,1341,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. a – d" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1253,1276]" captionTargetBox="[195,1386,213,1213]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1409,193,1232]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 1. a – d. Kapsa (Rigida? aculeiformis Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; e – h. Kapsa (Rigida) apicispina Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; i – l. Kapsa (Rigida) brevis Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; m – q. Kapsa (Rigida? explanata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222871/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
Fig. 
<number box="[1105,1117,1341,1365]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
o, p) almost reaching tip of vertex. Face (
<figureCitation box="[303,366,1377,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. a – d" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1253,1276]" captionTargetBox="[195,1386,213,1213]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1409,193,1232]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 1. a – d. Kapsa (Rigida? aculeiformis Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; e – h. Kapsa (Rigida) apicispina Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; i – l. Kapsa (Rigida) brevis Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; m – q. Kapsa (Rigida? explanata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222871/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
Fig. 
<number box="[355,366,1377,1401]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
q) comparatively short, midline of frontoclypeal area and lower part of anteclypeus dark.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1305,1908]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
Abdominal apodemes short, extended to 
<number box="[693,707,1416,1440]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" value="4.0">4</number>
th sternite. Anal tube appendage (
<figureCitation box="[1110,1185,1416,1440]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1026,1049]" captionTargetBox="[178,1413,205,990]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[168,1419,193,1005]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Kapsa (Rigida) explanata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage and anal tube appendage, lateral view; c. subgenital plate, paramere, connective and the 9 th sternite, dorsal view; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. paramere, lateral view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222879/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
Fig. 
<number box="[1170,1185,1416,1440]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
a, b) large and long, exceeding hind margin of pygofer side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1305,1908]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
Pygofer dorsal appendage (
<figureCitation box="[510,578,1488,1512]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1026,1049]" captionTargetBox="[178,1413,205,990]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[168,1419,193,1005]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Kapsa (Rigida) explanata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage and anal tube appendage, lateral view; c. subgenital plate, paramere, connective and the 9 th sternite, dorsal view; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. paramere, lateral view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222879/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
Fig. 
<number box="[563,578,1488,1512]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
a, b) straight and short, tapering towards apex. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[1316,1385,1488,1512]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1026,1049]" captionTargetBox="[178,1413,205,990]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[168,1419,193,1005]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Kapsa (Rigida) explanata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage and anal tube appendage, lateral view; c. subgenital plate, paramere, connective and the 9 th sternite, dorsal view; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. paramere, lateral view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222879/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
Fig. 
<number box="[1370,1385,1488,1512]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
a, d) with 
<number box="[213,227,1524,1548]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" value="6.0">6</number>
macrosetae, lateral margin with setae-free region medially. Apex of paramere (
<figureCitation box="[1176,1248,1524,1548]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1026,1049]" captionTargetBox="[178,1413,205,990]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[168,1419,193,1005]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Kapsa (Rigida) explanata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage and anal tube appendage, lateral view; c. subgenital plate, paramere, connective and the 9 th sternite, dorsal view; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. paramere, lateral view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222879/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
Fig. 
<number box="[1234,1248,1524,1548]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
e) footlike, heel expended, approximately the same length as anterior point. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[957,1022,1560,1584]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1026,1049]" captionTargetBox="[178,1413,205,990]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[168,1419,193,1005]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Kapsa (Rigida) explanata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage and anal tube appendage, lateral view; c. subgenital plate, paramere, connective and the 9 th sternite, dorsal view; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. paramere, lateral view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222879/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
Fig. 
<number box="[1009,1022,1560,1584]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
f) broad, manubrium short. Aedaegal shaft (
<figureCitation box="[226,299,1596,1620]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1026,1049]" captionTargetBox="[178,1413,205,990]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[168,1419,193,1005]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Kapsa (Rigida) explanata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. pygofer dorsal appendage and anal tube appendage, lateral view; c. subgenital plate, paramere, connective and the 9 th sternite, dorsal view; d. subgenital plate, dorsal view; e. paramere, lateral view; f. connective; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222879/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[284,299,1596,1620]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="9.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" unit="g" value="9.0">9</quantity>
</figureCitation>
g, h) straight, denticulate distally, with tiny fin-shaped protrusion dorsally; dorsal apodeme well developed, ventral process extremely small, flattened in lateral view; gonopore terminal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1305,1908]" box="[199,737,1668,1692]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,371,1668,1692]" pageId="15" pageNumber="132">Measurement.</emphasis>
Body length: males 3.0– 
<quantity box="[653,733,1668,1692]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="15" pageNumber="132" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
